:{{DIcon|undefined}} It's about the Dragon Lady?
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 202030502: Config/Level/Mission/2020305/Act/Act202030502.json-->
::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 101 m.ogg}} {{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 101 f.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Yes, you have extraordinary skills, and you earned her trust when you rescued her...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Earned her trust? When did that happen?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050103-->
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 102.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' You rescued her from the mara-struck... I'd say she's forever in your debt.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 103.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' If you go see her, I'm sure she won't run away.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why do people here keep making me run errands?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050106-->
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 104.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' If I had more people, I wouldn't have to ask for external help. But as things stand...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Okay, I'll do it!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050108-->
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 105.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Hah, that was fast! Thanks for your help.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_202050109-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050109-->
::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 106.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Here's the situation: Lady Bailu, the Vidyadhara Dragon Lady, has escaped from the Alchemy Commission again. I say "again" because the Realm-Keeping Commission has seen more than a few of her bad-tempered escapes.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_202030502_20-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_202030502_20-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Vidyadhara?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050111-->
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 107.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' This must be your first time on the Xianzhou... It's a long story. The Vidyadhara is one of the three races that established the Xianzhou Alliance.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 108.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Their bloodline is different from us Xianzhou natives. The Vidyadhara are born with great vitality, the gift of the Permanence, as they say.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 109.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' That's all you need to know. The rest is irrelevant to what's happening today.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What does a Dragon Lady do exactly?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050115-->
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 110.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' A Dragon Lady... isn't an official position. People address her that way out of love.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 111.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' The Vidyadhara "high elder," on the other hand, is a position similar to a chief &mdash; it's been passed down from generation to generation. But only the Vidyadhara that possess draconic features and inherit the dragon heart can be successors.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 112.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' And Miss Bailu is the Vidyadhara's future high elder on the Luofu.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 113.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' The rumor has always been that she can heal the wounded merely by touching them and shedding tears. She also studied medicine in the Alchemy Commission. That's why her other title is "Healer Lady."
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} She escaped? Was she imprisoned?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050120-->
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 114.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Not imprisoned exactly... Vidyadhara customs are somewhat different from Xianzhou native customs. Miss Bailu has incredible talents and is next in line to rule over the Vidyadhara &mdash; it's normal that her people would want to keep a close eye on her.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 115.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' However, she also has a somewhat free spirit... She always manages to find a way to escape her residence.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm listening.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050123-->
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 116.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' It used to be the duty of the Realm-Keeping Commission to go after her and take her back to the Alchemy Commission.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 117.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' But, this time is different. Because of the Stellaron crisis, we're constantly short of manpower. Besides, even if we catch the Dragon Lady, we can't take her back anytime soon.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 118.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' I don't know if you heard &mdash; someone locked down the delves connected to the Alchemy Commission.
:::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 119.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Now nobody can get in or out &mdash; it's completely cut off. Something very fishy is going on.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_202030502_39-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_202030502_39-->
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} So how did the Dragon Lady get out?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050128-->
::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 120.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' That's what I want to know. I guess she sneaked out before the delves were locked down. She might even know what happened in the Alchemy Commission...
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} But I saw doctors...
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050130-->
::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 121.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Those doctors came from apothecaries in other delves. I've asked them, and they don't have the slightest clue what's going on.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Then... is there really anything I can do?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050132-->
::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 122.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' I'd like you to help with two things. First, find the Dragon Lady and take care of her until the Alchemy Commission delves are reopened. Don't lose sight of her.
::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 123.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' The second thing might be a bit hard to understand... I want you to stop her from treating the mara-struck.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_202030502_48-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_202030502_48-->
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Can't the Realm-Keeping Commission take care of her?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050135-->
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 124.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Like I said &mdash; we don't have enough people! The Dragon Lady is smart. If we try to keep her in the Realm-Keeping Commission Chancery, she'll sneak out the first chance she gets. Trust me, it's happened before...
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 125.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Besides, it isn't a crime for her to run away from her residence. And even if it were, given her status, we couldn't exactly stick her in jail and throw away the key! You're the only person we can turn to.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why stop her from treating the mara-struck?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050138-->
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 126.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Being stricken with mara isn't like catching a curable disease. All the Healer Lady can do is slow the process.
:::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It's not a disease?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050140-->
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 127.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Take you short-life species as an example. Do you consider aging a disease?
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 128.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Aging can be slowed, but it's still unavoidable &mdash; just like being stricken with mara for the people of the Xianzhou... Unfortunately, becoming mara-struck is more terrifying than death. It's an inevitable curse in the blood of Xianzhou natives.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Then, what can be done for them?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050143-->
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 129.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' The Xianzhou has long had other methods. When mara is about to strike, the spiritfarers and judges of the Ten-Lords Commission promptly take the afflicted away. It's not something the Alchemy Commission should be meddling in.
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 130.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Mara is scary, but it won't cause any harm if you have it under control. We have the Realm-Keeping Commission and Cloud Knights here in Exalting Sanctum &mdash; more than enough to handle any eventuality.
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 131.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' However, the Dragon Lady's mara-suppression could lead to mara-struck falling under the Ten-Lords Commission's radar. If we let her carry on, we'll have mara-struck on every street corner &mdash; people will panic!
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 132.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Seeing as we're already dealing with one crisis, we need to be extra vigilant when dealing with the mara-struck. This is not something that can be taken lightly.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I see. Leave it to me.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050148-->
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 133.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' You're the distinguished guest of General Jing Yuan and Diviner Fu Xuan. As such, you also have the full trust of the Realm-Keeping Commission.
:::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 134.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Oh, one more thing... There's a lot of suspicion surrounding the Alchemy Commission these days. If you discover someone from the commission on the hunt for the Dragon Lady, watch your step.
:::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It'll be a piece of cake.
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050151-->
::::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 135.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Great!
:::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Babysitting? No thanks, I'd rather watch paint dry.
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050153-->
::::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 136.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' There's no other way. The Realm-Keeping Commission will pay you handsomely for your help.
:::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I have a feeling this is more complicated than it sounds...
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202050155-->
::::::{{A|VO side2 bl1 dahao 137.ogg}} '''Dahao:''' Bah, don't fret. Looking after children is a pain, but as the general's distinguished guest, I know you'll do great.
:::::<!--Custom String Trigger: ALL_TALK_END-->
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: ALL_TALK_END-->
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: ALL_TALK_END-->
:::::<!--Custom String Trigger: 202010301_Finish-->
:::::<!--Ends the current performance-->
:::::<!--Custom String Trigger: 202010301_Finish-->
:::::<!--Ends the current performance-->
