:{{DIcon}} I've got a few things to ask.
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502020103: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G43/Act/Act_502020103.json-->
::'''Dahao:''' I won't be able to answer if it's too difficult. You can ask Officer Jingyan instead.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502020101_32-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502020101_32-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What does an officer do every day?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020121-->
:::'''Dahao:''' Officers are managers in the Chancery, responsible for coordinating all local internal and external affairs &mdash; that's the surface definition. Actually, the main job involves going to meetings at the Realm-Keeping Commission's General Affairs Office and spreading their ideas.
:::'''Dahao:''' Honestly, I'm not very good at these clerical jobs. I used to be the leader for a Cloud Knight squad that reported directly to General Jing Yuan. Are you surprised? I'm like a fish in water when it comes to weaponry. Not when it comes to office meetings.
:::'''Dahao:''' However, veteran soldiers are far more likely than everyday citizens to be stricken with mara &mdash; something to do with post-traumatic stress. Anyways, it's very dangerous.
:::'''Dahao:''' So they transferred me here to be an officer. There's no life-or-death situations here, but it ain't easy work. I don't know exactly what I'm doing, but I know that I'm busy.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Officer Jingyan seems very capable.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020126-->
:::'''Dahao:''' She's the most capable girl I've ever met. No matter what the job is, she will get it done.
:::'''Dahao:''' She used to be my subordinate back when I was still in the Cloud Knights, and she came over with me when I was transferred to the Realm-Keeping Commission. I taught her everything I knew, but for some reason she chose to stick around...
:::'''Dahao:''' Sometimes I even wonder whether this work at the Realm-Keeping Commission is hindering her future career prospects. But I've never actually said it out loud, and she's become an indispensable part of the Chancery.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Officer Songyan doesn't seem very motivated?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020130-->
:::'''Dahao:''' That little punk wasn't always this way. Apparently he used to be an elite at the General Affairs Office &mdash; but he became completely demotivated after some kind of setback, and was transferred to our jurisdiction.
:::'''Dahao:''' At any other workplace, he'd be cast aside for being so lazy, right? But I want to give him some more time. He's just not ready yet.
:::'''Dahao:''' We have no way of really understanding him, but at least we can give him "enough time," be it decades or centuries. That's one of the few great benefits of living in a long-life society.
:::'''Dahao:''' Of course, I don't think time alone is enough to solve every problem. If he doesn't make changes for himself, then the problems he's facing will never change either.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} That's enough chit-chat.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502020135-->
:::'''Dahao:''' Alright, it's time for me to watch the news anyway. See you later.
:::<!--Ends the current performance-->
